And came unto Iconium. The metropolitan city of Lycaonia, situated at Mount Taurus, whereof, among others, the famous Amphilochius was bishop, who under Theodosius the Great was most vehement against heresies, and of an eminent authority, as it doth appear even by the third law, De Fide Catszolica. Lycaonia of old, a part of Pisidia, hath Pisidia upon the west, Isauria upon the south, Cappadocia the second upon the east, and upon the north, Galatia Secunda, called also The Healthy.
